===============================================================================

Blazer::Querygen has been installed!

Next steps:

1. Set your OpenAI API key as an environment variable:
   export OPENAI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

   Or add to .env file:
   OPENAI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

2. Configure the initializer if needed:
   config/initializers/blazer_querygen.rb

3. Include the JavaScript in Blazer's layout:

   Create app/views/layouts/blazer/application.html.erb:

   <!DOCTYPE html>
   <html>
   <head>
     <title>Blazer</title>
     <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
     <%= csp_meta_tag %>
     <%= stylesheet_link_tag "blazer/application" %>
     <%= javascript_include_tag "blazer/application" %>
     <%= javascript_include_tag "blazer/querygen/prompts" %>
   </head>
   <body>
     <%= yield %>
   </body>
   </html>

   Note: This overrides Blazer's default layout to include our JavaScript.

4. Add to asset precompile (config/initializers/assets.rb):
   Rails.application.config.assets.precompile += %w[blazer/querygen/prompts.js]

5. Restart your Rails server:
   rails restart

6. Navigate to Blazer's "New Query" page and you'll see the AI generation UI!

Troubleshooting:
- If JavaScript doesn't load, check browser console for errors
- Verify OPENAI_API_KEY is set: rails c > ENV['OPENAI_API_KEY']
- Check health endpoint: /blazer/querygen/health

For more information, visit:
https://github.com/mat_aki/blazer-querygen

===============================================================================
